He also wrote several dramas, which were acted by Macready, Miss Cushman and other stars, but they did not meet with great popular favor· Browning 15 distinguished for the depth of his spiritual insight, his dra- matic energy and power of psychological analysis. His style is fre- quently obscure and difficult, his versification hard and rugged, and his rhymes forced. Browning died December 12, 1889, at Venice, the very day his last volume of poems was published, and was buried in West- minster Abbey.

An extended correspondence with Elizabeth Barrett, the poetess, led to love and an engagement before Browning ever met her. The two were clandestinely married in 1846 and made their home in Florence.
